    "body": "Thanks @JustinDrake and @wangyinglike1234.\r\n\r\nI think we should restructure the docs to push users to run their own eth1 nodes. Whilst providing a sigp-hosted eth1 node is nice for usability in testnets, it's not an accurate reflection of mainnet. Relying upon some centrally hosted API (e.g., our geth node on AWS) for eth1 -> eth2 linking is a major centralization risk. Whomever controls that eth1 node will control eth2 validator on-boarding. Allowing this corner-cutting is dishonest (for lack of a less harsh word) and gets users in bad habits.\r\n\r\nIf we _do_ decide to continue to supply a public eth1 node, we should probably spin up a few of them in different zones (US, Europe, Asia) and let users pick one that's close to them. I suspect the ",
